lonesome /ˈləʊnsəm/

1. ADJ Someone who is lonesome is unhappy because they do not have any friends or do not have anyone to talk to. 孤寂的 [美国英语] [usu v-link ADJ] 

例： I've grown so lonesome, thinking of you. 我从小到大都很孤单，经常想起你。 

2. ADJ A lonesome place is one which very few people come to and which is a long way from places where people live. 荒僻的 [美国英语] 

例： He was finding the river lonesome. 他发现这条河很偏僻。

